model_diff:
*   **Map Overview**
    *   The map illustrates the number of US Americans reporting ancestry from various European countries (3 of 3 GPT, 3 of 3 Claude, 3 of 3 Gemini), based on self-reported data from the 2019 American Community Survey (3 of 3 Claude).

*   **Highest Ancestry Group**
    *   Germany is most frequently identified as the country with the highest number of US Americans claiming ancestry, reported at 45,000,000 (3 of 3 GPT, 2 of 3 Claude, 3 of 3 Gemini). However, Ireland was also cited as the highest source, with figures of 31,000,000 (1 of 3 GPT) or 54,000,000 (1 of 3 Claude).

*   **Reported Ancestry Numbers**
    *   Specific ancestry numbers reported for European countries include: Germany with 45,000,000 (3 of 3 GPT, 3 of 3 Claude, 3 of 3 Gemini); Ireland with 31,000,000 (2 of 3 GPT) or 34,000,000 (1 of 3 GPT, 1 of 3 Claude, 3 of 3 Gemini) or 54,000,000 (1 of 3 Claude); and England or the United Kingdom with 24,000,000 (1 of 3 GPT), 34,000,000 (2 of 3 Claude), or 54,000,000 (3 of 3 Gemini), with the UK also noted as the second highest source at 34,000,000 (1 of 3 Claude). Additional figures include Italy at 16,000,000 (3 of 3 Claude, 3 of 3 Gemini), 17,000,000 (2 of 3 GPT), or 18,000,000 (1 of 3 GPT); Poland at 9,000,000 (3 of 3 GPT, 3 of 3 Claude, 3 of 3 Gemini); France at 8,000,000 (2 of 3 GPT, 3 of 3 Claude, 3 of 3 Gemini) or 10,000,000 (1 of 3 GPT); Russia at 2,000,000 (3 of 3 GPT, 2 of 3 Gemini); Norway at 3,400,000 (2 of 3 Claude) or 4,500,000 (2 of 3 GPT); Sweden at 3,400,000 (1 of 3 Claude), 3,800,000 (2 of 3 GPT, 1 of 3 Claude), or 3,900,000 (1 of 3 Claude); Greece at 1,200,000 (3 of 3 GPT, 1 of 3 Claude, 3 of 3 Gemini); Spain at 1,000,000 (3 of 3 Gemini) or 1,300,000 (1 of 3 Claude); Ukraine at 1,100,000 (1 of 3 GPT, 2 of 3 Claude); Iceland at 54,000 (1 of 3 Claude, 1 of 3 Gemini); Portugal at 1,300,000 (2 of 3 Gemini); Denmark at 1,200,000 (1 of 3 Claude); the Netherlands at 3,200,000 (1 of 3 Claude) or 5,000,000 (1 of 3 GPT); and Romania at 1,100,000 (1 of 3 Gemini).
